  "prompt": "In reaction, [math]N_2 O_4\\to {2NO_2}_{(g)}[/math], what will be the value of [math]K_C[/math] at 35\u00b0 C if [math]N_2 O_4[/math] is dissociated to the extent of 20% under a pressure of 1 atmosphere?",
  "response": "To find the value of the equilibrium constant \\( K_C \\) for the reaction \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\to 2 \\text{NO}_2 \\) at 35\u00b0C, we will start by determining the concentrations of the reactants and products at equilibrium. \n\nGiven:\n- Initial pressure of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) (which can be considered as its initial concentration before dissociation) = 1 atm\n- Fraction dissociated of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) = 20% or 0.20\n\nFirst, let's define the initial concentration of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\):\n\\[ [\\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4]_{\\text{initial}} = 1 \\text{ atm} \\]\n\nBecause \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) is dissociated by 20%, the amount dissociated is:\n\\[ \\text{Dissociated amount of } \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 = 0.20 \\times 1 = 0.20 \\text{ atm} \\]\n\nAt equilibrium, the concentration of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) is:\n\\[ [\\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4]_{\\text{eq}} = 1 - 0.20 = 0.80 \\text{ atm} \\]\n\nFor every mole of \\( \\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4 \\) dissociated, 2 moles of \\( \\text{NO}_2 \\) are produced:\nThe concentration of \\( \\text{NO}_2 \\) formed will be:\n\\[ [\\text{NO}_2]_{\\text{eq}} = 2 \\times (0.20) = 0.40 \\text{ atm} \\]\n\nNow we'll use these equilibrium concentrations to find the equilibrium constant \\( K_C \\):\n\\[ K_C = \\frac{[\\text{NO}_2]^2}{[\\text{N}_2\\text{O}_4]} \\]\n\nSubstitute the equilibrium concentrations into the expression:\n\\[ K_C = \\frac{(0.40)^2}{0.80} = \\frac{0.16}{0.80} = 0.20 \\]\n\nTherefore, the value of \\( K_C \\) at 35\u00b0C is 0.20.",
